The paper discusses methods for interpreting machine learning models, which falls under the broad category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus on uncertainty in the interpretations suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). The use of public datasets for text classification and recidivism risk-scoring suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of cryptography and security (cs.CR), cybernetics (cs.CY), and information retrieval (cs.IR).
